The White House has released a statement announcing that President Obama will meet with the Secretary General of NATO, Mr. Jaap de Hoop Scheffer, on March 25, 2009. The purpose of the meeting is to discuss preparations for the upcoming 60th anniversary NATO Summit in Germany and France, as well as to review the status and strategy of NATO missions. The President is committed to NATO and wants to ensure that the Alliance remains relevant in addressing 21st century security challenges.